{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3a4f72a9-34a4-414f-a38a-b6a330fcd21d","content":"Here's the setup:\n\n**AppShell.xaml**\n```xml\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<Shell\n    x:Class=\"MyApp.AppShell\"\n    xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n    xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n    xmlns:views=\"clr-namespace:MyApp.Views\"\n    FlyoutBehavior=\"Flyout\">\n\n    <!-- Dashboard: single page in its own section -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Dashboard\" Icon=\"dashboard.png\">\n        <ShellContent\n            Title=\"Dashboard\"\n            ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:DashboardPage}\"\n            Route=\"dashboard\" />\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n    <!-- Products: two tabs (Active / Archived) -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Products\" Icon=\"products.png\">\n        <Tab Title=\"Products\">\n            <ShellContent\n                Title=\"Active\"\n                ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:ActiveProductsPage}\"\n                Route=\"active\" />\n            <ShellContent\n                Title=\"Archived\"\n                ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:ArchivedProductsPage}\"\n                Route=\"archived\" />\n        </Tab>\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n    <!-- Settings: accessible from flyout -->\n    <FlyoutItem Title=\"Settings\" Icon=\"settings.png\">\n        <ShellContent\n            Title=\"Settings\"\n            ContentTemplate=\"{DataTemplate views:SettingsPage}\"\n            Route=\"settings\" />\n    </FlyoutItem>\n\n</Shell>\n```\n\n**AppShell.xaml.cs** — register the detail route:\n```csharp\nnamespace MyApp;\n\npublic partial class AppShell : Shell\n{\n    public AppShell()\n    {\n        InitializeComponent();\n\n        // Register routes not in the visual hierarchy\n        Routing.RegisterRoute(\"productdetails\", typeof(Views.ProductDetailsPage));\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Navigating to the details page** (e.g. from ActiveProductsPage):\n```csharp\nawait Shell.Current.GoToAsync($\"productdetails?id={product.Id}\");\n```\n\n**Receiving the parameter** in `ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs`:\n```csharp\n[QueryProperty(nameof(ProductId), \"id\")]\npublic partial class ProductDetailsPage : ContentPage\n{\n    public string ProductId { get; set; }\n}\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n| Element | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `FlyoutItem` | Top-level flyout entry |\n| `Tab` with multiple `ShellContent` | Bottom tab bar within a flyout item |\n| `Routing.RegisterRoute` | Enables navigation to pages not in the shell visual tree |\n| `ContentTemplate` + `DataTemplate` | Lazy-loads pages on first visit |\n\nThe `Tab` wrapper inside the Products `FlyoutItem` gives you the bottom tab strip with \"Active\" and \"Archived\". Dashboard and Settings each have a single `ShellContent`, so no tabs appear for those.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8f7f645c-9c70-4b73-939f-2fe53bd56d54","outputTokens":748,"requestId":"A85B:1D8045:6FB62E:80B807:69FBE4A2"},"id":"d0f87333-52e1-47ec-9558-534f160f56d8","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:02:39.203Z","parentId":"3e398bc7-d94b-47ec-8d0c-232ce0c18bfb"}
